1. Q: Which of the following is a way of referencing a commit?
A: i. using full SHA-1 hash
ii. using HEAD pointer
iii. using short SHA-1 hash

2. To explore a tree listing that will return the list of files at a specific point, you would use "git ls-tree HEAD".

3. If you want to look at a specific commit to see what changed and what the commit was all about, you would use "git show".
